article.headline: CS Northridge 64, UC Riverside 50
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Kenny Daniels scored 17 points as Cal State Northridge defeated UC Riverside 64-50 Thursday night. Lenny Daniel added 10 points and eight rebounds for the Matadors (6-10, 1/3 Big West), who outscored the Highlanders 14-0 over the final 5:14. Kyle Austin led Riverside (7-9, 1-3) with 18 points while Sean Cunningham had 11. Bryson Hampton hit two free throws with 15:39 remaining to give the Highlanders a 42-36 lead, their largest of the game. Riverside then went scoreless over the next 7:51, and Northridge went up 45-42. The score was tied 50-all with 5:14 to play when Northridge's defense took over and didn't allow Riverside to score again.
